anvas> to contain the ellipses, you can use ellipse elements (and all the other shape elements) with any <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Panel> or <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Control> that supports non-text content.  \n  \n This example is part of a larger sample; for the complete sample, see [Shape Elements Sample](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=160037).  \n  \n## See Also  \n <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse>   \n <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Shape>   \n [Shape Elements Sample](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=160037)","nodes":[{"pos":[12,64],"content":"How to: Draw an Ellipse or a Circle | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"How to: Draw an Ellipse or a Circle | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,52]}]},{"pos":[550,585],"content":"How to: Draw an Ellipse or a Circle","linkify":"How to: Draw an Ellipse or a Circle","nodes":[{"content":"How to: Draw an Ellipse or a Circle","pos":[0,35]}]},{"content":"This example shows how to draw ellipses and circles by using the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse&gt;</ph> element.","pos":[586,696],"source":"This example shows how to draw ellipses and circles by using the <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse> element."},{"content":"To draw an ellipse, create an <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse&gt;</ph> element and specify its <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Width%2A&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Height%2A&gt;</ph>.","pos":[697,889],"source":" To draw an ellipse, create an <xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Ellipse> element and specify its <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Width%2A> and <xref:System.Windows.FrameworkElement.Height%2A>."},{"content":"Use its <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Shapes.Shape.Fill%2A&gt;</ph> property to specify the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Media.Brush&gt;</ph> that is used to paint the interior of the ellipse.","pos":[890,1049],"source":" Use it